an evolving form of political organisation, is perpetuated as part of this situation.Representing differentiated, unique and exclusive examples of the (r)evolutionary phenomenon of neo-jihadism, Al Qaeda and Islamic State are characteristic of the mutually constitutive nature of ‘power and resistance’. Just as resistance movements throughout modern history come to resemble the forms of power they sought to overthrow, so too have Al Qaeda and Islamic State reconstituted the dominant political-economic paradigm of neoliberalism they mobilised in response to.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIslamic fundamentalismxEconomic aspects. 0aTerrorismxEconomic aspects. 4aPolitical Studies 2021. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  aBourdieu.  aanti-capitalism.  adialectics.  afinance.  aneo-Marxism.  aneo-jihadism.  aneoliberalism.  apolitical economy.  apolitical violence.  apropoganda.1 aRichards, Imogen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614321140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526143211423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526143211/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles